# Collapsed side-rail icon symmetry

When changing **collapsed** left (`.sidebar`) or right (`.character-studio-sidebar`) icon strips:

## Invariant

**Left and right collapsed icon columns must mirror each other** — same width, icon size, gap, padding, and vertical start so row *N* on the left aligns with row *N* on the right.

## Shared tokens (define on `.app` only)

| Token | Purpose |
|-------|---------|
| `--collapsed-rail-width` | Collapsed rail width (both sides) |
| `--collapsed-rail-icon-width` / `--collapsed-rail-icon-height` | Icon button size (match scene-controls hamburgers: 40×40) |
| `--collapsed-rail-icon-gap` | Vertical gap between icons |
| `--collapsed-rail-icon-padding` | Icon column padding |

Do **not** add per-side overrides (e.g. extra `padding-top: 3rem` on one rail only).

## Shared selectors (keep in sync)

Style both rails together:

- Containers: `.collapsed-sidebar-icons`, `.collapsed-character-studio-icons`
- Buttons: `.sidebar-icon`, `.character-studio-sidebar-icon`
- Collapsed width: `.sidebar.collapsed`, `.character-studio-sidebar.collapsed`

## Layout rules

1. **No ghost hamburger space** — in-panel hamburgers (`.hamburger-menu`, `.character-studio-sticky-hamburger`) use `display: none` when collapsed; scene-controls row hamburgers are the active controls.
2. **No asymmetric top offsets** — do not reserve space for hidden hamburgers with large `padding-top` on one side only.
3. **Right rail vertical origin** — `.character-studio-sidebar` uses `top: var(--app-chrome-top-height)` (header + scene-controls), not header alone.
4. **Spacing via gap only** — use `gap` on the icon column; avoid extra `margin-bottom` on individual icons on one side.

## Checklist when adding/changing collapsed icons

1. Add or update icons on **both** rails if the feature is paired, or document intentional asymmetry.
2. Change shared `--collapsed-rail-*` tokens instead of one-off pixel values.
3. Keep container + button rules in the **shared selector blocks** in `App.css`.
4. Verify visually with **both panels collapsed**: icons form horizontal pairs across the viewport.
